      "text": "1. Wiki is [[Exciting and addictive]] to a small subset of authors. They find the experience of writing in wiki compelling.\n1. The majority of writers are not prepared to sustain the level of confusion created by the [[Interface quirks]] of the current implementation.\n1. Small group-work around a [[Common research goal]] is able to motivate individuals to persevere with writing.\n1. The onboarding experience needs to encourage and motivate some difficult. initial tasks like writing an [[Author Page]].\n1. Some authors find that wiki meets there need for [[Solipsistic writing]].\n1. The [[Social aspect of wiki]] is best supported by social processes, and not simply software engineering. "
